---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import BottomCTA from '../components/BottomCTA.astro';
---

<Base title="Scope & Lifecycle — Coherence by Viewyonder" description="Where things live, when they activate, and what each session can see. Understand how user, project, and session scopes interact.">
  <article class="container guide">
    <header class="guide-header">
      <a href="/" class="back-link">&larr; Home</a>
      <p class="section-label">Guide</p>
      <h1>Scope & Lifecycle</h1>
      <p class="guide-subtitle">
        Where things live, when they activate, and what each session can see.
      </p>
    </header>

    <nav class="toc">
      <p class="toc-title">On this page</p>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="#diagram">How the layers fit together</a></li>
        <li><a href="#marketplace">1. Add the marketplace</a></li>
        <li><a href="#install">2. Install the plugin</a></li>
        <li><a href="#restart">3. Restart Claude Code</a></li>
        <li><a href="#init">4. Run /coherence</a></li>
        <li><a href="#other-sessions">5. Other sessions</a></li>
        <li><a href="#other-repos">6. A different repo</a></li>
        <li><a href="#teammates">7. Teammates</a></li>
        <li><a href="#quick-reference">Quick reference</a></li>
        <li><a href="#confusion">Common confusion points</a></li>
      </ul>
    </nav>

    <div class="prose">

      <!-- ============================================ -->
      <section id="diagram" class="guide-section">
        <h2>How the Layers Fit Together</h2>

        <div class="scope-diagram">
          <div class="scope-layer scope-user">
            <div class="scope-label"><span class="scope-badge scope-badge-user">USER</span> ~/.claude/</div>
            <div class="scope-desc">All repos, all sessions</div>
            <div class="scope-files">
              <code>settings.json</code> <span class="file-note">marketplace source + enabled plugins</span><br />
              <code>plugins/cache/viewyonder-coherence/</code> <span class="file-note">cached plugin code + skills</span>
            </div>

            <div class="scope-layer scope-project">
              <div class="scope-label"><span class="scope-badge scope-badge-project">PROJECT</span> ~/your-project/</div>
              <div class="scope-desc">This repo only</div>
              <div class="scope-files">
                <code>.claude/hooks/</code> <span class="file-note">enforcement hooks</span><br />
                <code>.claude/agents/</code> <span class="file-note">review agents</span><br />
                <code>.claude/skills/coherence/</code> <span class="file-note">local skill dispatcher</span><br />
                <code>.claude/settings.local.json</code> <span class="file-note">hook registrations</span><br />
                <code>CLAUDE.md</code> <span class="file-note">project instructions</span><br />
                <code>docs/SPEC-*.md</code> <span class="file-note">architectural specs</span>
              </div>

              <div class="scope-layer scope-session">
                <div class="scope-label"><span class="scope-badge scope-badge-session">SESSION</span> Claude Code instance</div>
                <div class="scope-desc">This terminal only</div>
                <div class="scope-files">
                  Loads <code>~/.claude/settings.json</code> <span class="file-note">sees plugin skills</span><br />
                  Loads <code>.claude/settings.local.json</code> <span class="file-note">sees hooks + local skills</span><br />
                  <span class="file-note">Must restart to pick up changes to either scope</span>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- ============================================ -->
      <section id="marketplace" class="guide-section">
        <h2>1. Add the Marketplace</h2>
        <p class="scope-tag"><span class="scope-badge scope-badge-user">USER</span> scope</p>

        <div class="terminal">
          <div class="terminal-header">
            <span class="terminal-dot"></span>
            <span class="terminal-dot"></span>
            <span class="terminal-dot"></span>
            <span class="terminal-title">Claude Code</span>
          </div>
          <div class="terminal-body">
            <span class="prompt">&gt;</span> /plugin marketplace add viewyonder/coherence
          </div>
        </div>

        <p>
          Writes an entry to <code>~/.claude/settings.json</code> under
          <code>extraKnownMarketplaces</code>. This tells Claude Code where to find Coherence.
          Applies to every session and every repo on this machine.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- ============================================ -->
      <section id="install" class="guide-section">
        <h2>2. Install the Plugin</h2>
        <p class="scope-tag"><span class="scope-badge scope-badge-user">USER</span> scope &mdash; the default</p>

        <div class="terminal">
          <div class="terminal-header">
            <span class="terminal-dot"></span>
            <span class="terminal-dot"></span>
            <span class="terminal-dot"></span>
            <span class="terminal-title">Claude Code</span>
          </div>
          <div class="terminal-body">
            <span class="prompt">&gt;</span> /plugin install coherence
          </div>
        </div>

        <p>
          Downloads the plugin to <code>~/.claude/plugins/cache/viewyonder-coherence/</code>
          and adds it to <code>enabledPlugins</code> in <code>~/.claude/settings.json</code>.
          User scope is the default &mdash; the plugin is available in every repo without re-installing.
        </p>

        <div class="callout">
          <strong>Install also enables.</strong> There is no separate enable step.
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- ============================================ -->
      <section id="restart" class="guide-section">
        <h2>3. Restart Claude Code</h2>
        <p class="scope-tag"><span class="scope-badge scope-badge-session">SESSION</span> scope</p>

        <p>
          Plugin skills won't appear until the session reloads its plugin registry.
          The safest way is to <code>/exit</code> and relaunch Claude Code.
          You can also try <code>/reload-plugins</code> if available in your version,
          but a full restart is the reliable path.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- ============================================ -->
      <section id="init" class="guide-section">
        <h2>4. Run <code>/coherence</code></h2>
        <p class="scope-tag"><span class="scope-badge scope-badge-project">PROJECT</span> scope</p>

        <div class="terminal">
          <div class="terminal-header">
            <span class="terminal-dot"></span>
            <span class="terminal-dot"></span>
            <span class="terminal-dot"></span>
            <span class="terminal-title">Claude Code</span>
          </div>
          <div class="terminal-body">
            <span class="prompt">&gt;</span> /coherence
          </div>
        </div>

        <p>
          This is the only step that writes to the current repo. It creates
          <code>.claude/hooks/</code>, <code>.claude/agents/</code>, <code>.claude/skills/</code>,
          <code>.claude/settings.local.json</code>, <code>CLAUDE.md</code>, and optionally
          <code>docs/SPEC-*.md</code> &mdash; all customized to your project's stack.
        </p>
        <p>
          Nothing touches other repos. Nothing touches <code>~/.claude/</code> beyond
          what the install step already did.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- ============================================ -->
      <section id="other-sessions" class="guide-section">
        <h2>5. Other Sessions in the Same Repo</h2>

        <p>If you open a second terminal in the same repo:</p>

        <ul class="check-list">
          <li><strong>The plugin skill</strong> (<code>/coherence</code>) works immediately if the plugin is installed and that session has loaded it (started after steps 2&ndash;3).</li>
          <li><strong>Hooks</strong> activate automatically &mdash; they're registered in <code>.claude/settings.local.json</code>, which every session reads from the repo.</li>
          <li><strong>If skills are missing</strong>, restart that session. The plugin registry is loaded at session start.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <!-- ============================================ -->
      <section id="other-repos" class="guide-section">
        <h2>6. A Different Repo</h2>

        <p>
          The plugin is installed at user scope, so <code>/coherence</code>
          is available in any repo.
          But no hooks, agents, or SPEC docs exist until you run <code>/coherence</code>
          in that repo.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- ============================================ -->
      <section id="teammates" class="guide-section">
        <h2>7. Teammates</h2>

        <p>
          Teammates install the plugin independently (steps 1&ndash;3). If your team commits
          the <code>.claude/</code> directory, they get hooks and agents immediately. If
          <code>.claude/</code> is gitignored, each teammate runs <code>/coherence</code>
          in their own checkout.
        </p>
        <p>
          The plugin itself is never shared via git &mdash; it's always per-user.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- ============================================ -->
      <section id="quick-reference" class="guide-section">
        <h2>Quick Reference</h2>

        <div class="ref-table-wrap">
          <table class="ref-table">
            <thead>
              <tr><th>Action</th><th>Scope</th><th>What It Affects</th></tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr>
                <td>Add marketplace</td>
                <td><span class="scope-badge scope-badge-user">USER</span></td>
                <td><code>~/.claude/settings.json</code> &mdash; all repos</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>Install plugin</td>
                <td><span class="scope-badge scope-badge-user">USER</span></td>
                <td><code>~/.claude/plugins/cache/</code> + <code>enabledPlugins</code> &mdash; all repos</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>Restart session</td>
                <td><span class="scope-badge scope-badge-session">SESSION</span></td>
                <td>Loads updated plugin registry</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><code>/coherence</code></td>
                <td><span class="scope-badge scope-badge-project">PROJECT</span></td>
                <td>Creates <code>.claude/</code>, <code>CLAUDE.md</code>, <code>docs/</code> &mdash; this repo only</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>Edit a hook</td>
                <td><span class="scope-badge scope-badge-project">PROJECT</span></td>
                <td><code>.claude/hooks/</code> &mdash; this repo only</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>Edit SPEC docs</td>
                <td><span class="scope-badge scope-badge-project">PROJECT</span></td>
                <td><code>docs/SPEC-*.md</code> &mdash; this repo only</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- ============================================ -->
      <section id="confusion" class="guide-section">
        <h2>Common Confusion Points</h2>

        <div class="faq-items">

          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3>"I installed the plugin but skills don't show up."</h3>
            <p>Restart Claude Code. The plugin registry is loaded once at session start.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3>"My other terminal doesn't have the plugin skills."</h3>
            <p>That session was started before the plugin was installed. Restart it.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3>"I ran init in one repo but my other project doesn't have hooks."</h3>
            <p><code>/coherence</code> is project-scoped. Run it in each repo that needs Coherence.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3>"Should I install as user scope or project scope?"</h3>
            <p>
              User scope (the default). This makes plugin skills available everywhere.
              The project-specific files are created by <code>/coherence</code>,
              not by the plugin install.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3>"Will this affect my teammate's setup?"</h3>
            <p>
              No. The plugin install is per-user (<code>~/.claude/</code>).
              Project files in <code>.claude/</code> can be committed to git if your team
              wants shared hooks, but each person installs the plugin independently.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3>"I updated the plugin but don't see new skills."</h3>
            <p>Restart Claude Code to reload the plugin cache.</p>
          </div>

        </div>
      </section>

    </div>
  </article>
  <BottomCTA />
</Base>

<style>
  .guide {
    padding-top: 7rem;
    padding-bottom: 4rem;
  }

  .guide-header {
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
  }

  .back-link {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    display: inline-block;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  .guide-subtitle {
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    font-size: 1.15rem;
    max-width: 50ch;
  }

  /* Table of contents */
  .toc {
    background: var(--bg-mid);
    border: 1px solid var(--bg-surface);
    border-radius: var(--radius);
    padding: 1.5rem 2rem;
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
    max-width: 500px;
  }

  .toc-title {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .toc ul {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
  }

  .toc li {
    margin-bottom: 0.4rem;
  }

  .toc a {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
  }

  .toc a:hover {
    color: var(--cyan);
    opacity: 1;
  }

  /* Sections */
  .guide-section {
    padding: 0;
    margin-bottom: 4rem;
    position: relative;
  }

  .guide-section h2 {
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .guide-section h3 {
    margin-top: 2rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .guide-section p {
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  /* Scope diagram */
  .scope-diagram {
    margin: 1.5rem 0 2rem;
  }

  .scope-layer {
    border-radius: var(--radius);
    padding: 1.25rem;
    margin-top: 1rem;
  }

  .scope-user {
    background: var(--bg-mid);
    border: 1px solid rgba(0, 255, 240, 0.2);
  }

  .scope-project {
    background: var(--bg-surface);
    border: 1px solid rgba(255, 0, 170, 0.2);
  }

  .scope-session {
    background: var(--bg-elevated);
    border: 1px solid rgba(255, 136, 68, 0.2);
  }

  .scope-label {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
  }

  .scope-desc {
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .scope-files {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    line-height: 1.8;
    color: var(--text-primary);
  }

  .scope-files code {
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    background: rgba(0, 255, 240, 0.06);
    padding: 0.1em 0.4em;
    border-radius: 3px;
  }

  .file-note {
    color: var(--text-muted);
    font-size: 0.75rem;
  }

  /* Scope badges */
  .scope-badge {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.6rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    padding: 0.15em 0.5em;
    border-radius: 3px;
    vertical-align: middle;
    margin-right: 0.4rem;
  }

  .scope-badge-user {
    background: rgba(0, 255, 240, 0.12);
    color: var(--cyan);
    border: 1px solid rgba(0, 255, 240, 0.3);
  }

  .scope-badge-project {
    background: rgba(255, 0, 170, 0.12);
    color: var(--magenta);
    border: 1px solid rgba(255, 0, 170, 0.3);
  }

  .scope-badge-session {
    background: rgba(255, 136, 68, 0.12);
    color: var(--orange);
    border: 1px solid rgba(255, 136, 68, 0.3);
  }

  .scope-tag {
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  /* Checklist */
  .check-list {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
  }

  .check-list li {
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    padding: 0.5rem 0;
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
    position: relative;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
  }

  .check-list li::before {
    content: "\25B8";
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: var(--cyan);
    font-size: 0.8rem;
  }

  .check-list li strong {
    color: var(--text-primary);
  }

  /* FAQ items */
  .faq-items {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  .faq-item {
    background: var(--bg-mid);
    border: 1px solid var(--bg-surface);
    border-radius: var(--radius);
    padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem;
  }

  .faq-item h3 {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
    color: var(--text-primary);
  }

  .faq-item p {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
  }

  /* Reference tables */
  .ref-table-wrap {
    overflow-x: auto;
    margin: 1rem 0 1.5rem;
    border-radius: var(--radius);
    border: 1px solid var(--bg-surface);
  }

  .ref-table {
    width: 100%;
    border-collapse: collapse;
    font-size: 0.875rem;
  }

  .ref-table thead {
    background: var(--bg-surface);
  }

  .ref-table th {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    text-align: left;
    padding: 0.6rem 1rem;
  }

  .ref-table td {
    padding: 0.55rem 1rem;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--bg-surface);
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    vertical-align: top;
  }

  .ref-table code {
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    background: rgba(0, 255, 240, 0.06);
    color: var(--text-primary);
  }

  /* Callout */
  .callout {
    background: var(--bg-mid);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--cyan);
    padding: 1rem 1.25rem;
    border-radius: 0 var(--radius) var(--radius) 0;
    margin: 1.5rem 0;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
  }

  .callout strong {
    color: var(--text-primary);
  }

  /* Terminal blocks */
  .terminal {
    background: var(--bg-deep);
    border: 1px solid var(--bg-surface);
    border-radius: var(--radius);
    overflow: hidden;
    margin: 0.75rem 0 1rem;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
  }

  .terminal-header {
    background: var(--bg-surface);
    padding: 0.5rem 0.75rem;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.4rem;
  }

  .terminal-dot {
    width: 8px;
    height: 8px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: var(--text-muted);
    opacity: 0.5;
  }

  .terminal-title {
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    margin-left: auto;
  }

  .terminal-body {
    padding: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.8;
  }

  .terminal-body .prompt {
    color: var(--cyan);
    user-select: none;
    margin-right: 0.5rem;
  }
</style>
